  "prompt": "A good friend of mine is gay , but we made out before telling me. Is there any chance he is bisexual ?",
  "response": "It's certainly possible that your friend could be bisexual. Someone's sexual orientation can be complex and doesn't always fit into neatly defined categories. The fact that you two made out could mean he has some level of attraction to people of your gender, but it doesn't necessarily define his entire sexual orientation.\n\nIt's important to remember that sexual orientation is a spectrum, and people can experience attraction in different ways. Some may identify as gay but still have had experiences or feelings towards people of different genders. Others may identify as bisexual, meaning they are attracted to more than one gender.\n\nThe best way to understand your friend's feelings is to have an open and respectful conversation with him. You might ask him how he identifies or if he's comfortable sharing more about his experiences and feelings. It's crucial to approach the conversation without making assumptions and to be supportive, whatever his orientation may be.",
